############ selinux commands ------------------------

### selinux
setenforce 0    ===> to set selinux in premissve mode for troubleshooting
getenforce      ===> to check se mode
to troubleshoot check selinux premission in /var/log/audit/audit.log
restorecon -R -v index.html   ### to restore label
semanage fcontext -a -t unconfined_u:object_r:admin_home_t:s0 index.html    ## premanently change label
chcon -t unconfined_u:object_r:admin_home_t:s0 index.html   ##temproray change label
getsebool -a | grep httpd     ==> more granular properties for selinux
setsebool ftpd_anon_write on

matchpathcon -V test.txt  ==> for troubleshooting it will check and verfied it is correct or not and suggest the correct context

semanage port -l


######### selinux port add

This will most likely be related to SELinux

semanage port -l | grep http_port_t
http_port_t                    tcp      80, 81, 443, 488, 8008, 8009, 8443, 9000
As you can see from the output above with SELinux in enforcing mode http is only allowed to bind to the listed ports. The solution is to add the ports you want to bind on to the list

semanage port -a -t http_port_t  -p tcp 8090

##add for nginx
semanage port -m -t http_port_t -p tcp 8200
























